<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry To Send Note to UN Secretary on Belize </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0203032994 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 0220 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0203032994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] <LOCATION>Guatemala City</LOCATION>, 1 Mar (DPA) -- It was officially 
reported today that the <ORGANIZATION>Guatemalan Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> will send a 
formal note to <ORGANIZATION>UN</ORGANIZATION> Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
expressing <LOCATION>Guatemala</LOCATION>'s interest in solving the 100-year-old 
territorial dispute with <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> through negotiations or 
international legal procedures. 
  Guatemalan Foreign Minister <PERSON>Gladys Marithza Ruiz de Vielman</PERSON> 
said that "in order to safeguard <LOCATION>Guatemala</LOCATION>'s rights regarding 
<LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>," the <ORGANIZATION>Ministry</ORGANIZATION> decided to send the note to the <ORGANIZATION>UN</ORGANIZATION> 
secretary general, "with the appropriate reservations regarding 
the territorial sea, the exclusive economic zone, and 
continental shelf, so that it can be circulated as an official 
document of the <ORGANIZATION>United Nations</ORGANIZATION>." 
  The government of Guatemalan President <PERSON>Ramiro de Leon Carpio</PERSON> 
maintains claims over the territory of <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> (23,000 square 
km), which <LOCATION>Great Britain</LOCATION> unilaterally granted independence on 21 
<DATE>September 1981</DATE>. <PERSON>Jorge Serrano Elias</PERSON>, the previous president who 
was ousted on 1 <DATE>June 1993</DATE>, recognized <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> and established 
diplomatic relations. Various Guatemalan sectors, including 
Human Rights <PERSON>Ombudsman Jorge Mario Garcia</PERSON> <LOCATION>Laguardia</LOCATION>, have said 
this was unconstitutional. 
  Moreover, because the border between the two countries has 
not been well defined, some incidents have occurred. The 
<ORGANIZATION>Guatemalan Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> reported that the <ORGANIZATION>Belizean 
Government</ORGANIZATION> has affirmed that a group of Guatemalans allegedly 
settled in Belizean territory. This is being investigated by the 
<ORGANIZATION>Guatemalan Government</ORGANIZATION>. 
  Human Rights <PERSON>Ombudsman Garcia</PERSON> <LOCATION>Laguardia</LOCATION> has asked for the 
immediate intervention of the <ORGANIZATION>Guatemalan Army</ORGANIZATION> to protect 
Guatemalan territory, after he personally learned of the threats 
that Belizean soldiers have issued against 35 families in the 
town of <LOCATION>Rio Hondo</LOCATION> in northern <ORGANIZATION>Peten Department</ORGANIZATION>, on the border 
with <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>. The ombudsman met with local peasants who provided 
details of the threats. Garcia <LOCATION>Laguardia</LOCATION> called for strict 
control and surveillance of the border area by the <ORGANIZATION>Army</ORGANIZATION> to 
guarantee the rights of the Guatemalans. 

</TEXT>

