<H3> <TI>   Belize Leaves Central American, EU Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belize Leaves Central American, EU Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3103040994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1254 GMT 29 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA3103040994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [Report by <PERSON>Lucia Perez Moreno</PERSON>] </F>
  [Text] <LOCATION>Athens</LOCATION>, 29 Mar (NOTIMEX) -- <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> today abandoned 
the 10th Central American and <ORGANIZATION>European Union</ORGANIZATION> [<ORGANIZATION>EU</ORGANIZATION>] Foreign 
Ministers' Meeting after <LOCATION>Greece</LOCATION>, the host country, withdrew its 
observer status. 
  The incident occurred after the Guatemalan delegation asked 
<PERSON>Theodoros Pangalos</PERSON>, current chairman of the <ORGANIZATION>European Council of 
Ministers</ORGANIZATION>, to withdraw <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>'s status as observer at the 
ministerial meeting. 
  "<LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>'s participation in the <LOCATION>San Jose</LOCATION> meetings will depend 
on the context of negotiations on the territorial dispute," it 
was stated to NOTIMEX by Guatemalan Foreign Minister <PERSON>Gladys 
Marithza Ruiz de Vielman</PERSON>. 
  <LOCATION>Guatemala</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> established diplomatic relations in 
<DATE>1981</DATE>, although the two countries have yet to settle a 
territorial dispute. 
  "We were invited by the council's chairman. We do not 
consider this the place to discuss differences between <LOCATION>Guatemala</LOCATION> 
and <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>," said <PERSON>Ursula Brown</PERSON>, <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>'s ambassador to the 
<LOCATION>United Kingdom</LOCATION>, shortly before her departure. 
  A participant in the meeting said <LOCATION>Greece</LOCATION> made "a mistake in 
formalities" when it invited <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> as an observer without first 
consulting with the Central American country. 
  The problem arose when the Belizean representative stood 
close to the <ORGANIZATION>EU</ORGANIZATION> and Central American foreign ministers when 
posing for a group picture of the meeting, which is currently 
being held at an elegant hotel on the outskirts of the Greek 
capital. 
  <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>, with a population of 200,000, achieved its 
independence from the <LOCATION>United Kingdom</LOCATION> in <DATE>1986</DATE>, and <LOCATION>Guatemala</LOCATION> has 
demanded the return of part of their common border since then. 
  Although <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> had been invited to participate as an 
observer in other international forums on <LOCATION>Central America</LOCATION>, this 
was the first time it had been invited to participate in the <LOCATION>San 
Jose Summit</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

