<H3> <TI>   President Creates Council on Belizean Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Creates Council on Belizean Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1006171094 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 8 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PA1006171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The <ORGANIZATION>National Council</ORGANIZATION> on <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> [<ORGANIZATION>Consejo Nacional</ORGANIZATION> de 
<LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>], <ORGANIZATION>CNB</ORGANIZATION>, was formally constituted yesterday after President 
<PERSON>Ramiro de Leon Carpio</PERSON> signed a decree creating this consultative 
and advisory organization under the <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION>. 
  Foreign Minister <PERSON>Maritza Ruiz de Vielman</PERSON> will chair the <ORGANIZATION>CNB</ORGANIZATION>, 
and its members are: Fernando Andrade Diaz-Duran, <PERSON>Roberto 
Bermejo Gonzalez</PERSON>, <PERSON>Eduardo Castillo Carriola</PERSON>, <PERSON>Edwin Fernando 
Guzman Ovalle</PERSON>, <PERSON>Alberto Herrarte Gonzalez</PERSON>, <PERSON>Roberto Herrera 
Ibarguen</PERSON>, <PERSON>Carlos Larios Ochaita</PERSON>, <PERSON>Jorge Lujan Munoz</PERSON>, <PERSON>Oscar 
Clemente Marroquin Godoy</PERSON>, <PERSON>Gabriel Orellana Rojas</PERSON>, <PERSON>Jorge Skinner 
Klee</PERSON>, and <PERSON>Francisco Villaran Kramer</PERSON>. These 12 individuals will 
be sworn in shortly. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>CNB</ORGANIZATION> was created by government Decree 259-94 that asserts 
that the territorial difference with <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> and the search for a 
solution that conforms to the Constitution's precepts is a 
matter of national interest. The purpose is to modernize and 
reorganize the <ORGANIZATION>CNB</ORGANIZATION> as a study, planning, consultative, and 
advisory office of the <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> for everything related 
to the territorial disagreement with <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>. 
  According to the decree, the <ORGANIZATION>CNB</ORGANIZATION> will be authorized to 
appoint permanent or temporary commissions or sub-commissions as 
well as take the necessary measures to regulate their work. The 
decree will take effect when it is published in the official 
daily. 

</TEXT>

