<H3> <TI>   Council on Belize To Study Border Dispute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council on Belize To Study Border Dispute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206015594 Guatemala City Teleonce Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2206015594 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Teleonce Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [From the "Telepress" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The <ORGANIZATION>National Council</ORGANIZATION> on <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>, which will be in 
charge of conducting a general and thorough evaluation of the 
dispute over that territory, was officially installed today. 
  An agreement to update and reorganize the <ORGANIZATION>National Council</ORGANIZATION> 
on 
<LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> specifies that the entity will do studies and planning 
and will advise the <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> on all matters related to 
the territorial dispute with <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>Council</ORGANIZATION> will be headed by Foreign Minister <PERSON>Gladys 
Maritza 
Ruiz de Vielman</PERSON> and will be made up of the following persons, 
who will work without compensation: <PERSON>Fernando Andrade Diaz 
Duran</PERSON>, <PERSON>Roberto Bermejo Gonzalez</PERSON>, <PERSON>Eduardo Castillo Arriola</PERSON>, <PERSON>Erwin 
Fernando Guzman Ovalle</PERSON>, (<PERSON>Alberto Errarte Gonzalez</PERSON>), <PERSON>Roberto 
Herrera Ibarguen</PERSON>, <PERSON>Carlos Larios Ochaita</PERSON>, <PERSON>Jorge Lujan Munoz</PERSON>, 
<PERSON>Oscar Clemente Marroquin Godoy</PERSON>, <PERSON>Gabriel Orellana Rojas</PERSON>, <PERSON>Mario 
Quinonez Amezquita</PERSON>, <PERSON>Jorge Skinner Klee</PERSON>, and <PERSON>Francisco Villagran 
Kramer</PERSON>. 
  The 8 <DATE>June</DATE> agreement states that the territorial dispute 
with 
<LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION> and the search for a solution within the framework of the 
Constitution and the principles of international law are matters 
of national interest. The document recognizes the 
appropriateness of the <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> receiving the advice of 
qualified citizens who, based on their knowledge and 
capabilities, can help formulate an adequate policy to resolve 
the territorial dispute with <LOCATION>Belize</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

